Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: python-sfor
Version: 0.1.3
Summary: Simple Failover Resolver
Home-page: http://pypi.python.org/pypi/python-sfor
Author: shinjiikeda
Author-email: gm.ikeda@gmail.com
License: LICENSE.txt
Description: Sfor
        ====
        
        Simple failover resolver for Python
        
        this is experimental version.
        yet, you should not use in large-scale service.
        
        
        
        Install
        ===
        
            pip install sfor
        
        Example
        ===
        
        
            from sfor.sfor_simple import SforSimple, SforNodeInfo
            import time
            import logging
            
            node_list = [
                SforNodeInfo("hoge1", 80, "/status.html"),
                SforNodeInfo("hoge2", 80, "/status.html"),
            ]
            
            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG, format='%(asctime)s %(message)s', datefmt='%m/%d/%Y %I:%M:%S %p')
            
            sfor = SforSimple(node_list)
            
            for n in range(60):
                 logging.info(sfor.resolv())
                 time.sleep(1)
        
        
